                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.001 Montero, Juan/3: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-08-21T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >August 21, 1931—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 4:54 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>96. My telegram number 95, August 18, 6 p.m. The Senate has refused to accept
                    resignation of Montero. Nevertheless as a candidate <pb facs="1023" n="909"
                        xml:id="pg_909"/> for the presidency he has insisted upon turning over the
                    power temporarily to the Minister of the Interior, Manuel Trucco, who becomes
                    Vice President until after the elections.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Culbertson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
